<p />
<h2><a name="Abstract"> Abstract </a></h2>
<p />
<em>Looks like this project is likely defunct, since Radio now has <a href="http://radio.userland.com/stories/storyReader$10854" target="_top">comments</a> and <a href="http://jake.editthispage.com/2002/02/23" target="_top">comment counts</a> integrated into it.</em>
<p />
I want comments in my Radio Userland weblog!  
<p />
Luckily, before I even really got started, <a href="http://radio.userland.com/stories/storyReader$10854" target="_top">they implemented it as a feature</a>.  There are still a few tweaks that the feature could stand to have, and I might still look into some alternative comment facilities since Radio allows this feature to be configured.  <a href="http://www.quicktopic.com" target="_top">Quick Topic</a> <a href="/twiki/bin/view/Main/XmlRpc">XmlRpc</a> API anyone?  Or, I might play around with comments using <a href="http://rateyourmusic.com/yaccs/#FAQ">YACCS</a>.
<p />
<h2><a name="Download"> Download </a></h2>
<p />
<ul>
<li> <a href="http://www.decafbad.com/twiki/pub/Main/CommentsInRadioUserland/radio_comment_count_pl.txt" target="_top">radio_comment_count_pl.txt</a>: <strong>Count comments for a Radio Userland post</strong>
<ul>
<li> Install on a webserver somewhere.  You could use my installation, for now.
</li>
<li> Go to your <a href="http://192.168.123.182:5335/system/pages/prefs?page=2.12">comments preferences</a> in Radio Userland and change your comment text to:
<ul>
<li>  <code>&lt;iframe scrolling="no" frameborder="0" width="100" height=25" src="http://www.decafbad.com/radio_comment_count.pl?refresh=90&amp;u=100566&amp;p=&lt;%itemNum%&gt; "&gt;&lt;noframe&gt;comment&lt;/noframe&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</code>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> Be sure to replace "100566" in the above URL with your Radio Userland user number
</li>
<li> You should now see comment totals.
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
